<title>SINGAPORE: OCBC jumps on 1-for-5 bonus issue.</title>
<headline>OCBC jumps on 1-for-5 bonus issue.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-03-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in OCBC Bank Ltd jumped to a high of Singapore $9.75 in early morning trade on Monday on the back of its proposed 1-for-5 bonus issue, said dealers.</p>
<p>After half an hour of trading, the shares were up 50 cents to S$9.60. Volume was a moderate 125,000 units.</p>
<p>The foreign tranche of OCBC touched a morning high of S$17.60 but quickly eased back to S$17.40, unchanged from its previous close.</p>
<p>The bank released sharply higher than expected profits for 1996 and had proposed a 1-for-5 bonus issue last week to celebrate its 65th anniversary.</p>
<p>OCBC reported a 17.2 percent rise in 1996 earnings to S$708.86 million.</p>
<p>- Singapore Newsroom 65-8703080</p>
